{"url": "https://www.reddit.com/r/learnprogramming/comments/9beis7/media_query_question/", "text": "If I\u2019m adding a media query for a website to be responsive to mobile devices, do I have to rewrite all of the CSS inside the media query and just change the ones I want? Or can I just change the ones I want and everything else will be the same?\n\nFor instance, say on a desktop I wanted my font size to be 40px, but on mobile I want it to be 20px... would I have to copy ALL of the other styling inside the media query, and only change the font size? I can explain further if needed.", "score": 1, "comments": [{"body": "     Or can I just change the ones I want and everything else will be the same? \n\n\u200b\n\nYes the media query will over-right the existing CSS and leave the rest as is.  It will also reverse this situation when it is not active.  An easy test is to simply change the background color and see how the query works.\n\n\u200b", "id": "e52fcc1", "replies": []}], "title": "Media query question"}